Anonymous Mon 24 May 2021 03:49:49 No.38905124 Report
Quoted By: >>38905311
>>38902549
Yes. It's my primary hunting rifle in areas that allow high powered rifles. I've taken a grizzly bear with it, three elk, two caribou, five antelope, more mule and white tail deer than I can count. One shot every time.

You have to know the cartridge you're using, be familiar with it and the rifle (meaning, a few hundred or a thousand rounds down a target range minimum). Shot placement is everything. There are big differences between a 150, 165, 180, and 220 grain bullet, and you better know the velocity and match the cartridge to your game.

I've butchered deer that were shot in the wrong place and a .30-06 spoils a lot of meat with bad shot placement. Frankly, it's an overpowered cartridge for whit tail deer & antelope, although it's great with a light 150 grain bullet out at 300 or 400 yards. I originally got it for mule deer and elk out in the Rockies where I expected to be shooting out at 200 or 300 yards usually.

It's borderline for a moose. Not because you can't kill a moose with it, but even with a really good shot, a moose can be pissed off enough to come after you at short range before it dies. You NEVER want to be attempting a second shot at something like a moose if it's close and charging you.

The grizzly, BTW, was not a planned hunt. It was after a mule deer I shot, and it noticed me. Like, too close and really showed far more interest in me than I was comfortable with, so I took it out before it could make up its mind. That was not a casual decision on my part. A big grizzly (this one was full grown, but not huge) is also borderline game for a .30-06. Not because it won't do the job, but a less-than-perfect shot will often piss them off enough to take you apart before the shot kills them. When you're limited to three shots, it's a bad day when you have to try and make the 2nd & 3rd count (especially with a bolt action). With a running target closing on you, you aren't likely to make those shots count in time and you won't get a 4th.
